properties.Name: TreasuryStock
properties.Description:
A corporation's own stock that has been issued, fully paid for, and reacquired by the corporation but not retired.

If the repurchased shares are not retired, they are designated as treasury stock and shown as an offsetting account in the stockholders' equity section of the balance sheet.

Columns.Name: LegalEntityId
Columns.Description:
The unique identifier of a Legal Entity.

In this case it is the business, organization or legal entity whose books are being recorded and financial statements presented.

Columns.Name: StockId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Financial Product.

Columns.Name: Timestamp
Columns.Description: The timestamp that the associated information is current or reported as-of.

Columns.Name: TotalNumberShares
Columns.Description: The total number of Treasury Stock shares held by the corporation as of the associated timestamp.
